==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[hyperbaton#Latin|hyperbaton]], from Greek [[ὑπερβατον]] ‘overstepping’, from [[ὑπερβαινειν]], from [[ὑπερ-]] + [[βαίνειν]] ‘walk’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/haɪˈpɜ:bətɒn/}}

===Noun===
'''hyperbaton'''
# (''Grammar, Rhetoric'') An inversion of the usual or logical order of words or phrases, for emphasis or poetic effect.